                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#203v #204r" facs="204"/>
                    <desc>
                    Medical prescriptions for stomach pain and Syphillis, written in Amharic, in an untrained hand. Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="am">መጽሐፈ፡ መድኃኒት፡ ውግዓት፡ ለሐመመ፡ አስረትን፡ እስኪ፡ ጠልቅ፡ የምስዋል፡ ሙጨ፡ የሚመስል፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#204v" facs="205"/>
                    <desc>
                    Asmat prayer against eye disease, in a trained hand. Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ <gap reason="omitted"/> ተወኪፈኪ፡ ስእለቶ፡ ወሀለወኪ፡ መንፈሳዊ፡ ዘቀብዓኪ፡ ዓይኖ፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#73v" facs="074"/>
                    <desc>
                    The midpoint of the Psalms is unmarked
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <desc>
                    The spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters in <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur#Chp118"/> are from the common new system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#147r #147v" facs="147 148"/>
                    <desc>
                    <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur#Chp151"/> has only the first of the four plusses that make up the long version, i.e., weadhanani
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <locus target="#152v" facs="153"/>
                    <desc>
                    The fourth biblical canticle is “[Prayer of Hana, mother of Samuel,] Prophetess.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <desc>
                    <title type="complete" ref="LIT2509Weddas"/> are laid out beginning with Monday and culminating with Sunday
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a7">
                    <locus target="#172v #199r" facs="173 199"/>
                    <desc>
                    The name <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኃይለ፡ ሥላሴ፡</foreign>, <persName ref="PRS1822IHA"/> is written by a secondary hand in the section divider
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    The manuscript has been donated to Hope College, Holland Michigan, where it as assigned the accession number TR2017.75.487.1
                    </desc>
                    </item>
